Usage
notify-send [-i ICON] [-t TIMEOUT] "TITLE" ["MESSAGE"]
Options:
ICON: specifies an icon to display. The possible values are: info | important | error. Default: info.

TIMEOUT: specifies the timeout in milliseconds at which to expire the notification. Default: 10000

TITLE: message title.

MESSAGE: message text.

Examples:
notify-send "My Message"

notify-send "Title" "Message"

notify-send -i error "Error" "File not found"

notify-send -i important "Attention!" "You should upgrade your software"
